Azure Portal:   https://portal.azure.com/#home
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Subscription vs Account:

Subscription is a logical container which contains the various resources you provision in the cloud such as VMs, DBs, Networks, etc.
Subscription can be attached to a lot of accounts. 

Account is an identity with access to resources in the subscription i.e. You. 
Account can be attached to a lot of subscriptions.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to create a resource group?

1) Search the resource group in the search box or go to the subscription and then search resource group
2) Click on Create resource group 
3) select the subscription , enter the resource group name, region 
4) Tags- Its optional to provide the Tags for the resource group
5) Click on Review and Create
6) It will show a notification of "Resource group has been created successfully". 

